Job Responsibilities:
Job responsibilities
Work collaboratively with the IT team and other business units to determine the scope, elicit the requirements, documentation, and implementation timeline of various IT projects;
Lead/facilitate business requirements workshops to understand the business requirements using a variety of techniques;
Translate business needs into clear functional and technical requirements for the developers to develop;
Create user stories / Tasks out of Business Requirements and support in scoping Sprints;
Work closely with developers during the development, testing, implementation and after go-live of the solution;
Responsible to conduct workload estimation for the projects;
Coordinate deliveries, training plan and all processes required for the releases;
Prepare documentation on expected benefits, use cases, current/proposed process, workflows, data flows alongside with the functional and non-functional specifications;
Document affected processes (current mode of operations vs future mode of operation) and procedures;
Participate in the creation of change management and training strategy.

Profile:
Profile
at least 3+ years of Experience as a Business Analyst, in the consumer product industry for retail, wholesale or manufacturing businesses;
University Degree or College Diploma, preferably in Computer Science or related discipline;
Certified Business Analysis Professional (CBAP), PMP or Scrum Master certification;
Experience with Business Process Reviews and requirements gathering, including the ability to use various techniques (JAD, interviewing, use case modeling, gap-fit analysis, data flow diagrams, process definition, etc.);
Experience in Jira, Confluence, Teamworks, Knowledge of SQL, prior experience with Desktop or Web applications will be an asset;
Strong interpersonal and team-building skills;
Analytical thinking, strong vision, communication skills and persuasiveness, to resolve issues with cross-functional teams;
Enthusiastic and positive attitude towards difficult tasks;
Fluent English oral and written; French or German are assets.
